<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="1181" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1181">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.113/4136</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Governor of California</gloss>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Executive Office</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Sacramento</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-04">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 4, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I am just in receipt of your
                            communication of April 26, suggesting that the appropriate officials of
                            this State be instructed to cooperate with the agents of the Federal
                            Government in the effort to prevent the illegal carrying of arms and
                            munitions of war into Mexico. Of course, I shall cheerfully do
                            everything possible in the premises, and will be very glad to comply
                            with any specific suggestions that you may make.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hiram W. Johnson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>